description: Prefer icon links over text links unless otherwise specified
alwaysApply: true
---

# Links as Icons

When adding links in the UI, use **icons** instead of text labels unless the user asks for text or the context clearly requires a text label (e.g. primary CTA, accessibility need).

## Do

- Use an icon (e.g. external-link, edit, delete, view) inside an `<a>` or `Link` with `aria-label` for accessibility.
- Keep the link target clear via tooltip or `aria-label`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: icon link with accessible label
<Link to={`/orders/${id}`} aria-label="View order">
  <ExternalLinkIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
</Link>
```

## Avoid

- Using raw text like "View", "Edit", "Open" as the only link content when an icon would suffice.

```tsx
// ❌ PREFER ICON: text-only link when icon would do
<Link to={`/orders/${id}`}>View order</Link>
```

## Exceptions

- Use text (or icon + text) when the user specifies it, when it's a primary call-to-action, or when the design system or accessibility requirements call for it.
